1
00:00:02,194 --> 00:00:06,952
When my old friend 
was visiting me

2
00:00:06,952 --> 00:00:11,422
and sharing that his faith
was damaged, and he was now …

3
00:00:11,582 --> 00:00:15,194
[Inconceivably Wonderful Creation]

4
00:00:15,194 --> 00:00:17,973
He said, “You know,
whether all of this,

5
00:00:17,973 --> 00:00:19,624
(meaning the world, everything)

6
00:00:19,624 --> 00:00:23,524
comes from God 
or just is, or … ”, he said,

7
00:00:23,524 --> 00:00:28,179
“They are both absurd to me.”
Like that.

8
00:00:28,239 --> 00:00:31,689
And I said, “Anyway … 
have some more chatni”.

9
00:00:31,689 --> 00:00:32,640
[Laughing]

10
00:00:33,238 --> 00:00:37,968
I didn’t choose at that time
to say anything, but later

11
00:00:37,975 --> 00:00:41,040
I was on a train in the Ukraine,

12
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:46,712
and I was thinking 
about this for months.

13
00:00:46,712 --> 00:00:50,707
And something came to me,
and I thought,

14
00:00:50,707 --> 00:00:54,242
“Yes”, I said,
“but you have something wrong—

15
00:00:54,242 --> 00:00:57,621
is that by dictionary definition

16
00:00:57,621 --> 00:01:01,730
that all of this just manifest
from nothing,

17
00:01:01,730 --> 00:01:04,730
that’s called absurd!”

18
00:01:04,730 --> 00:01:08,770
And on that point I must say:
brahma satya jagan mithyā—

19
00:01:08,779 --> 00:01:14,572
Śaṅkarācārya said, “I will now …
There are so many books written:

20
00:01:14,572 --> 00:01:16,822
Vedanta, the Upaniṣads,
this, that …

21
00:01:16,822 --> 00:01:19,791
Now in a half a line,

22
00:01:19,791 --> 00:01:22,451
I am going to tell you
everything you need to know.

23
00:01:22,451 --> 00:01:23,871
You can read
the Mahābhārata,

24
00:01:23,871 --> 00:01:25,849
you can read the Vedas,
you can read all of it.

25
00:01:25,849 --> 00:01:29,371
I’m going to tell you in a half a line,
not even in whole ṣloka,

26
00:01:29,371 --> 00:01:33,121
in half a line
I’m going to tell you everything.

27
00:01:33,141 --> 00:01:38,060
This is all you need:
brahma satya jagan mithyā—

28
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:43,060
spirit is truth, 
the world is false.

29
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:47,714
That’s all you need to know,
follow this line of thought.“

30
00:01:47,724 --> 00:01:53,520
But so, in a similar vein I thought,
“Yes, that all this came from nothing—

31
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:57,522
by dictionary definition
that is absurd.

32
00:01:57,537 --> 00:02:07,007
But that all of this is the creation 
of the Supreme Personality of Godhead,

33
00:02:07,007 --> 00:02:09,866
that is what we call inconceivable.”

34
00:02:09,866 --> 00:02:13,126
Not absurd, inconceivable,

35
00:02:13,127 --> 00:02:15,727
and inconceivably wonderful.

